<TITLE> Amanullah, Shahidul get bail on appeal against graft convictions </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 10 (bdnews24.com)- The High Court Monday granted three months' bail on Monday to former BNP state minister Amanullah Aman and former MP Mufti Shahidul Islam on appeals against convictions for amassing illegal wealth. Trial courts sentenced Amanullah to 13 years and Shahidul to 10 years behind bars in cases filed by the Anticorruption Commission. The Appellate Division rejected the ACC's appeal on Monday to overturn a High Court order granting bail to former BNP ministers Dr Khandker Mosharraf Hossain and Altaf Hossain Chowdhury and staying the proceedings of the Barapukuria coalmine case against them. bdnew
